 to his followers, but ruthless towards his enemies. He welcomed advice from diverse sources in his quest for world domination, for which he believed the shamanic supreme deity Tengri had destined him. The Mongol army under Genghis killed millions of people, yet his conquests also facilitated unprecedented commercial and cultural exchange over a vast geographical area. He is remembered as a backwards, savage tyrant in Russia and the Arab world, while recent Western scholarship has begun to reassess its previous view of him as a barbarian warlord. He was posthumously deified in Mongolia; modern Mongolians recognise him as the founding father of their nation.","createdAt":"2026-03-11T03:13:44.057Z","id":"cmmlgsp6h0001ryxzqcsmc167","summary":"Genghis Khan (born Temüjin; c. 1162 – 1227) founded and was the first khan of the Mongol Empire. After a challenging early life marked by his father's death and family abandonment, he united the Mongol tribes, overcoming conflicts with former allies to become the sole ruler of the Mongolian steppe by 1206.\n\nAdopting the title \"Genghis Khan,\" he reformed the tribal structure into a meritocracy and launched a series of military campaigns. His conquests included large parts of China (Western Xia, Jin Dynasty) and Central Asia (Qara Khitai, Khwarazmian Empire), with his forces reaching Georgia and Kievan Rus'. He died in 1227 while subduing the rebellious Western Xia.\n\nGenghis Khan remains a controversial figure: known for his ruthless conquests that killed millions, yet also for unifying the Mongols, facilitating vast commercial and cultural exchange, and being recognized as the founding father of Mongolia.","title":"chingeskhan","updatedAt":"2026-03-11T03:13:44.057Z","user":{"email":"ankhaa3334@gmail.com","id":"cmmlgsozn0000ryxzhencb9ob","name":"Ankhnyam Ankhaa"},"userId":"cmmlgsozn0000ryxzhencb9ob"}],"success":true}
