At":"2026-03-11T10:30:03.049Z","id":"cmmlwdt0q0000jixzf1j7o3l5","summary":"The Secret History of the Mongols recounts the origin of the Mongol people, beginning with Börte Chino and his wife Goo Maral, who crossed the sea, settled at the source of the Onon River near Burkhan Khaldun, and had a son named Batachikhan.\n\nThe lineage continued through figures like Dobu Mergen and his wife Alun-gua. After Dobu Mergen's death, Alun-gua bore three more sons, attributing their divine conception to a \"white-yellow man\" from heaven. Her youngest son, Bodonchar Munkhag, is identified as the founder of the Borjigin clan.\n\nFurther descendants include Haidu, whose son Chirkhai Liankhua gave rise to the Taichuud clan. Tumbinai Setsen's son, Kabul Khan, ruled the Khamag Mongol and founded the Khiyad Borjigin clan. Kabul Khan's grandson was Yesukhei Baatar, Chinggis Khan's father, who led the Khiyad Borjigin.\n\nDuring Chinggis Khan's unification of the Mongol tribes and establishment of the state, several influential feudal nobles were also Khiyad Borjigin, descendants of Kabul Khan, and thus relatives of Chinggis Khan.","title":"`","updatedAt":"2026-03-11T10:30:03.049Z","userId":"cmmlgsozn0000ryxzhencb9ob"},"message":"Article created","success":true}
